</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> The position of the image relative to the media edge is drifting 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> The media is not wound correctly 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-75E5BDE8-76A4-4922-92D3-7B8DB876FE8C" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Functional Logging (if available)</title><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Media Step Accuracy</b> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">In case there is a difference the media step errors between the left and right side of the media (Orange and Blue line) this might point to Y-movement of the media. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">In the graph below this can be seen in the first 3.5 meters of this print. 
</p><fig id="GUID-A9F2ED4D-1694-417D-AA97-C7AE7A0A09B8" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-9887738B-AC37-48DC-B652-2DCABBB7D30E-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-9887738B-AC37-48DC-B652-2DCABBB7D30E-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p "> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Buffer plate
</p><p class="- topic/p ">
</p><p class="- topic/p ">In case the drifting is caused by the media input (Drawer or Jumbo roll) the performance of the buffer plate is also deviating (see example below). 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">In those cases the orange (right side of the buffer plate) and the blue line (left side of the buffer plate) are not parallel. 
</p><fig id="GUID-218BB190-6B0C-431E-9CFF-31A24178360E" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-5B890039-DCD1-4333-8313-6D5177E4544F-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-5B890039-DCD1-4333-8313-6D5177E4544F-low.png"/></fig></section><section id="GUID-36EBDAEE-0F97-4B84-B3A4-97EDC261D340" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">ADAM-triggers</title><p class="- topic/p ">No available ADAM-triggers 
