</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Check the performance of the buffer plate 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><xref keyref="15ADJU004" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-DCF00A51-9FFA-40C1-BEA7-097A8EFB8F9F.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 15 How to check / adjust the buffer plate?>15 How to check/adjust the buffer plate</xref> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Functional logging ref C)</b>
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">26 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Adjust buffer plate 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><xref keyref="15ADJU004" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-DCF00A51-9FFA-40C1-BEA7-097A8EFB8F9F.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 15 How to check / adjust the buffer plate?>15 How to check/adjust the buffer plate</xref> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Functional logging ref C)</b>
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">27 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Decision 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Check if the media is not sticking to the rear covers. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Load a media roll on the printer. Preferably use IJM613 media or MPI2000 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Select: Print without winding. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Start Print job 
</p></li></ul></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">28 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Connect rear covers to electrical ground. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">29 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Decision 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Confirm the jumbo roll is used instead of the drawer 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">30 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Adjust Jumbo-roll 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Function logging Ref D)</b>
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Functional logging References:</b> 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">A)</b> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">In case the media is telescoping this is also visible in the performance of the buffer plate. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">In such case the left and right side of the media are not parallel (see example of “buffer plate” below). 
</p><fig id="GUID-295B2B6D-73C5-4618-927C-8BA5EAFE6C5E" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-1516AF43-1D58-4F7E-84F4-5C86E060342F-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-1516AF43-1D58-4F7E-84F4-5C86E060342F-low.png"/></fig></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">B)</b> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> In case the media is running smoothly over the platen the “media step accuracy” should show two parallel lines (see example below). 
</p><fig id="GUID-039B3C7F-5C4C-4452-B970-FFA806BA8F90" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-A849C562-CD67-45DF-A915-15883AE573AD-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-A849C562-CD67-45DF-A915-15883AE573AD-low.png"/></fig></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">C)</b> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> In case the buffer plate is in a static position the sensors of left and right side of the buffer plate should be same value (difference Orange and Blue lines &lt;30). 
</p><fig id="GUID-E3B19965-7001-4CC4-A55E-6EBF8B531E8D" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-FCBC3AB8-3155-4CCC-A055-EB112247323A-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-FCBC3AB8-3155-4CCC-A055-EB112247323A-low.png"/></fig></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">D)</b> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> When the Jumbo roll is aligned correctly and working within specification the “buffer plate” should show two parallel lines (see example below). 
</p><fig id="GUID-A169AF02-D777-4C57-9A56-1378DA402B28" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-07B48506-E9C1-4FBA-8E43-C6BE8AD0F13B-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-07B48506-E9C1-4FBA-8E43-C6BE8AD0F13B-low.png"/></fig></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-2513E5DF-C282-453D-9841-6E539DB0EB51" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Evaluate/Prevention</title><p class="- topic/p ">During installation the engine should be aligned correctly (platen horizontal and no torsion). During usage of the engine the customer should maintain the engine according to the care/use poster. 
</p></section><section id="GUID-987F83F9-80F0-41BC-B82B-BB16DA268203" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Background info</title><p class="- topic/p ">The position of the image on the media is controlled by the buffer plate in combination with the winder. The buffer plate will automatically steer the media towards the center of the platen. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The winder will wind the media on a output-core. If the winder is not working well (eg: Defective shaft or not aligned correctly) the winder is able to pull the media out of the center. This will result in a drifting position or bad winder quality. As the deviations in media position are stacking during the print the amount of drifting increases during the length of the print. 
</p></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-00803BE3-C849-4315-B1B2-2BBE04B8DBA4.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Solutions</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
